### Description

When using a table in a card, the table has its own background color resulting in different background colors.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/03f02917-b5cf-45aa-8da2-6ab867607de5)

### Reproduction

StackBlitz link:  https://stackblitz.com/edit/8i5einea?file=src%2Fexample%2Fcard-fancy-example.ts

### Expected Behavior

Bckground color of table should match card background color.

### Actual Behavior

Background color doesn't match.

### Environment

- Angular: 19.2.3
- CDK/Material: 19.2.7
- Browser(s): Chrome
- Operating System (e.g. Windows, macOS, Ubuntu): macOS

### Work-around

```
html {
  @include mat.card-overrides((
    elevated-container-color: var(--mat-sys-surface)
  ));
}
```
or
```
.mat-mdc-card {
  @include mat.table-overrides((
    background-color: transparent
  ));
  @include mat.paginator-overrides((
    container-background-color: transparent
  ));
}
```
